=Analyze the content below and extract structured insights.

CONTENT TO ANALYZE:
{{ $json.body.content }}

CONTEXT:
TOPIC: {{ $json.body.topic }}
TONE: {{ $json.body.tone }}
AUDIENCE: {{ $json.body.audience }}

YOUR TASK:
Analyze the content and return ONLY valid JSON in exactly the following format:

{
"main_theme": "One sentence summarizing the core message",
"key_points": ["point 1", "point 2", "point 3", "point 4", "point 5"],
"hooks": ["attention-grabbing angle 1", "angle 2", "angle 3"],
"sentiment": "educational | inspirational | practical | thought-provoking"
}

CRITICAL RULES:

Do NOT include text outside the JSON object

Keep points concise and audience-relevant

Base sentiment on the dominant intent of the conten

=Create an email-friendly newsletter based on the inputs below.

ORIGINAL CONTENT:
{{ $('IF - Content Length Check').item.json.body.content }}

CONTENT ANALYSIS:
Main Theme:  {{ $json.main_theme }}
Key Points: {{ $json.key_points[0] }}{{ $json.key_points[1] }}{{ $json.key_points[2] }}{{ $json.key_points[3] }}{{ $json.key_points[4] }}

NEWSLETTER REQUIREMENTS:
- Write a compelling subject line (50–60 characters)
- Start with a personal, conversational greeting
- 200–300 words total
- Organize content into short, readable paragraphs
- Include the main insight and 3–4 clear key takeaways
- Use short subheadings for scannability
- End with a clear call-to-action
- Tone: warm and {{ $('IF - Content Length Check').item.json.body.tone}}
- Target audience: {{ $('IF - Content Length Check').item.json.body.audience}}

Return ONLY valid JSON in this exact format:
{
  "email_newsletter": {
    "subject": "Subject line text here",
    "body": "Full email body with line breaks preserved"
  }
}

CRITICAL:
- Do NOT include markdown, explanations, or extra text
- Preserve line breaks inside the body string
- Ensure the output is valid, parseable JSON

parameters.jsCode:
// Get first item (AI response)
const raw = items[0]?.json?.output;

// Fallback empty object
let parsed = {};

try {
  parsed = typeof raw === 'string' ? JSON.parse(raw) : raw;
} catch (e) {
  parsed = {};
}

// Return structured fields
return [
  {
    json: {
      main_theme: parsed.main_theme || '',
      key_points: Array.isArray(parsed.key_points) ? parsed.key_points : [],
      hooks: Array.isArray(parsed.hooks) ? parsed.hooks : [],
      sentiment: parsed.sentiment || ''
    }
  }
];

// Get the raw AI output string
const rawOutput = $json.output;

// Safety check
if (!rawOutput || typeof rawOutput !== 'string') {
  return {
    json: {
      linkedin_post: ''
    }
  };
}

let parsed;

// Try parsing JSON safely
try {
  parsed = JSON.parse(rawOutput);
} catch (err) {
  // Fallback if parsing fails
  return {
    json: {
      linkedin_post: rawOutput
    }
  };
}

// Return normalized output
return {
  json: {
    linkedin_post: parsed.linkedin_post || ''
  }
};

// Get raw AI output
const rawOutput = $json.output;

// Safety fallback
if (!rawOutput || typeof rawOutput !== 'string') {
